---
name: scljet-sql-real-literal
description: SclJet REAL number literals in SQL text (INSERT / WHERE / SELECT / arithmetic); matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet REAL literals

The lexer reads a `digits.digits` fraction as a REAL literal (value carried on the token, parsed in
Double space), so real literals work in `VALUES`, `WHERE`, projections, and arithmetic — not just as
bound parameters or pre-built `SqlReal` rows. Integer-valued reals render with a trailing `.0`
(`10.0`), matching the sqlite3 CLI. Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 on the same
SQL (verified out-of-band); locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlReal, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows, executeMutation](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "prod", "CREATE TABLE prod(id INTEGER, price REAL)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlReal(1.5)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val db = apply(db0, "INSERT INTO prod VALUES (2,2.75),(3,10.0)")
    show(db, "SELECT id, price FROM prod ORDER BY id")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM prod WHERE price > 2.0 ORDER BY id")
    show(db, "SELECT price + 0.5 FROM prod WHERE id = 1")
    show(db, "SELECT 3.5")
    show(db, "SELECT 2.5 + 1.25")
    show(db, "SELECT id, price FROM prod WHERE price = 10.0")
```
